Don’t let your issues impact that. It’s mentally abusive to not respect someone’s pronouns, name, etc. and if they continue to subject themselves to it, it’s self harm.

Transitioning is about the one going through it, not the ones adjusting to it. While yes, their feelings of discomfort through this change are valid, that’s on them to deal with. The one transitioning has enough to deal with, learn, and cope with.

They’re trying to actively remind you, generally in a kind way. You’re not being attacked, harmed, or hurt by them reminding you. However, depending on what you say and what others hear, your trans loved one might be hurt physically or mentally. It might cost them their life.

However, sometimes there is the opposite to that. The one who gets defensive and feels attacked. Don’t do that. 

When you get a nudge or you’re flat out told that you need to watch what you’re saying, that person isn’t saying you aren’t trying.

Then they inevitably harm their trans loved one and the relationship implodes. 

There are some that listen, and they act on the new information well. When the loved one says “This isn’t nice, right, etc.” they actively try to adjust. That’s supportive.

There are many sources for support for those that are transitioning. Not so many for spouses, parents, or relatives. It can cause relationships to suffer, because those relations want to be supportive, but don’t know how.

Just let us live our lives. Put your efforts to stopping bad people. Not discriminating against those that mean no harm. Love one another. Care about your neighbor. Hug your friends and family. But most importantly, be excellent to each other.

In conclusion, this is just the ramblings of a girl that has too much on her mind. Who’s constantly watching people come after her community’s rights. Constantly worrying about where the next attack is coming from.

Christianity is synonymous with bigot these days. Too many using it to justify discrimination with word olympics. Christianity is supposed to be a beacon of hope. A symbol of love. A family devoted to caring. Not this perversion we have today.

Christianity is always used to justify trans discrimination. But it’s always twisted words. People only want to follow every letter when it’s useful to them. They forget that God asks for us to love and care for one another overall.

Stop going after people for being trans. Detransitioning does happen after backlash too. Sometimes it’s not misdiagnosis. Look to Christine Daniels. She transitioned, then detransitioned after being treated like crap and losing her family. It ended in her suicide.

Even though I’m just switching doctors for whatever reason. 

The best thing you can do for trans kids is to support the process. Help fund research into the best terms of care. Accept people for who they are. Stop ridiculing us over making a “decision” you wouldn’t have.

Extremists try to use detransitioners against us. But the thing is, those rates aren’t accurate. They compile them from people that stop treatment, even if it’s because they transfer doctors. If I were to go from the endo that I see, to a GP, I’d be counted as a detransitioner.
Is it perfect? Hell no. No treatment is. Are the misdiagnosis? Statistically there has to be. But if any other treatment had the success rate of transitioning, it would be hailed as a “miracle”.

When I started to accept being trans, I wanted them to “fix my brain”. I begged for it. I feared transitioning. But they explained my condition with the science behind it. Explained what they do know. Explained why transitioning is the number one treatment for dysphoria.

I’m very privileged to be able to go through HRT. I thank God every day that I found my way. Very different, in contrast to before I transitioned, I begged for it all to end quite frequently. HRT isn’t poison. It’s not “over medicating”. It’s a treatment.

I’m very reserved, when speaking about trans topics now. There’s fear of backlash, sure. But mostly, I just want to be me. Nothing more than that. I want to live. I want to find love. I want to have a family of my own someday.

I had so many questions in the beginning and lots of internalized transphobia to figure out and work out. Some people were willing to help me with that. Many were not. Can I blame them? Absolutely not. “Ignorance” is one of the many tools extremists use to gaslight us.
